Using this polyfill, one can link to media elements on a web page
using fragment identifiers containing media fragments, using URLs like
<http://example.org/podcast.html#episode1&t=01:23>.

Usage requires giving an “id” attribute to HTML media elements and
embedding the script at the bottom of the page, like:

<audio id=episode1 controls>
  <source src=episode1.oga type=audio/ogg>
  <source src=episode1.mp3 type=audio/mpeg>
</audio>

<script src=media-fragments-html-polyfill.js></script>